Package: dsVert
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Server-Side Functions for Vertically Partitioned Data
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Sarrat González", email = "david.sarrat@isglobal.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Miron", "Banjac", email = "miron.banjac@isglobal.org",
           role = "ctb"),
    person("Juan R", "González", email = "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org",
           role = "ctb")
  )
Description: Server-side DataSHIELD functions for privacy-preserving analysis
    of vertically partitioned federated data. The product AggregateMethods
    surface covers ECDH-PSI record alignment, GLM, Cox PH, negative binomial,
    multinomial, ordinal, LMM, GEE, GLMM, IPW, multiple imputation, LASSO,
    contingency, correlation, PCA, and descriptive aggregates. MPC kernels use
    additive secret sharing over Ring63 or Ring127 fixed-point arithmetic with
    Beaver triples and DCF wide-spline primitives. Historical diagnostic
    helpers that could reveal per-observation working values are removed from
    the invocable server surface.
